        <h2 id="verdict">Is MarketMuse worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For enterprise content teams: yes.</strong> Topic Authority is the most strategically useful metric in content SEO, and the briefs are deeper than anything else on the market. If you have 4+ writers and an executive who cares about coverage breadth, MarketMuse earns its $149–$399/mo.</p>

        <p><strong>For mid-market teams: maybe.</strong> Pair Standard ($149) with Surfer for execution. Total stack lands around $240/mo — pricey but workable if you have writers.</p>

        <p><strong>For small businesses: almost always no.</strong> You will spend $149+ on briefs that your one writer cannot keep up with. A done-for-you platform delivers finished articles for less than the brief budget alone.</p>

