        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is MarketMuse?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>MarketMuse is a content intelligence platform that uses AI to analyse topical authority, identify content gaps, and generate research-backed briefs. It maps the full semantic landscape of a topic before a writer touches a keyboard — answering "do I have authority here" rather than "do I rank for this keyword".</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">How much does MarketMuse cost in 2026?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Standard is $149/mo, Team plans start at $399/mo, and enterprise plans run higher with custom pricing. There is no public free tier; a limited free account exists for trial-only exploration.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Does MarketMuse write articles?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. MarketMuse generates AI-powered briefs — extremely detailed ones — but it does not write the article. Writers still draft, edit, and publish. The brief is the deliverable.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is Topic Authority?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Topic Authority is MarketMuse's proprietary score that measures how comprehensively a domain covers a subject. Higher scores correlate with higher rankings on related queries. It is the metric MarketMuse uses to recommend which topics to cover next.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">MarketMuse vs Surfer SEO — which is better?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Surfer scores content you've already drafted against the SERP. MarketMuse plans what to write before drafting. They solve different problems. Most enterprise teams that can afford both use Surfer for execution and MarketMuse for strategy.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Is MarketMuse worth $149/mo in 2026?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For enterprise content teams with writers and a strategic mandate — yes. For small business owners or solo operators — no. The real cost lands at $2,549–$7,899/mo once writers, editors, and publishing are added.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Does MarketMuse include AI writing?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>MarketMuse has a First Draft module that generates an outline-driven AI draft from a brief. Output quality is acceptable but still needs human editing — most teams use it as a structured starting point, not as the final article.</p></div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is the best MarketMuse alternative?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For SERP-based scoring at lower cost: Surfer SEO ($89/mo) or Clearscope ($170/mo). For done-for-you content publishing: theStacc ($99/mo). For cluster-style planning: Frase ($45/mo) or Machined ($49/mo).</p></div></div></div>
